    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, i guess. but it still feels like there's something weird going on because the math doesn't seem to add up to me. like, if my interest rate is X and my payment is Y, why is the principal reduction so tiny in the first few years? is there some kind of hidden factor or extra charge that's eating into the payment before it even reaches the principal?",
